I"î<h2 id="uncomplicated-pls-for-design">Uncomplicated PLs For Design</h2>
<p>Design only needs two kinds of data:</p>
<ul>
  <li>a thing</li>
  <li>a bunch<sup id="fnref:bunch" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:bunch" class="footnote">1</a></sup> of things.<br />
Anything more is deliterious.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="tell-pls-that-are-too-complicated">Tell: PLs That Are Too Complicated</h2>
<p>Any language that <em>encourages</em> you to use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">+</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">array</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">cons</code> or <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">...</code> is too complex for most design applications.</p>

<p>That kind of PL should only be used for <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">implementation</code>, not for design.</p>

